name: Green Treefrog (whitelip)
description: An environmental portrait of a baby green treefrog, which was photographed in the rainforest of northern Australia and became the centrepiece of this composition. Digital organic photography, Jpeg 1800px x 1200px.White Lipped Green Treefrog (Litoria infrafrenata) The whitelips are the largest tree frogs in the world and they can live for over 10 years in their native habitat. They reach lengths between 10 and 14 cm and vary in colour from bright green to brown with a paler colour underside. The have a very deep loud barking call and a distinctive white stripe that runs along their lower lip and over to their shoulder. Their large pads on their fingers and toes enable them to climb and do their acrobatics.@Naturesface2
